<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-15T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-15T08:00:00-05:00" n="764" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d764">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3465: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-15T13:00:00+00:00">October 15, 1936—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 15—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>X–217. My telegram No. X–122, September 4, 3 p.m. <hi rend="italic">Note verbale</hi> just received from Foreign Office encloses
                                copy of official reports of activities Government Air Forces based
                                on airfields in South namely Alcazares (Cartagena), Almeria,
                                Valencia, Guadix (Cordoba front) and Malaga on August 30, last. None
                                of operations reported included area near where destroyer <hi rend="italic">Kane</hi> was attacked.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wendelin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>